Vattenfall AB would take two or three
years to wind down operations in Poland if it decides to pull
out of the country, Jacek Piekacz, head of the largest Nordic
utilityâ€™s Polish unit, told reporters in Warsaw today, adding
that a decision will be made next year at the earliest.  Vattenfall has cancelled two planned coal-fired generation
